<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Part of the front of a <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> garland <rs type="objectType">sarcophagus</rs>, broken at either side and below: see <bibl>Isik 75</bibl> for fuller description.
</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> along the upper edge (surviving width of inscription, <measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre">0.70</measure>). In the second line the cutter has had to avoid elements of the decorative relief. The full text muxt have begun on the lid, and finished on the lower moulding.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p><measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.02</measure>, neatly cut</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>Probably
<date notBefore="0234" notAfter="0267" exact="none">middle third century</date>
 (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">spelling</rs>).</p>
</div>
